    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it all the way to the final round for our Senior DevOps role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They had really strong technical skills and a great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with Kubernetes orchestration. Can you draft something that is professional and kind but firm, so they don't feel like they wasted their time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior DevOps Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior DevOps role at our Austin office. We were genuinely impressed by your technical skills and the positive culture fit you demonstrated throughout the interview process. Your dedication and enthusiasm were evident, and we appreciate the time and effort you invested in our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with Kubernetes orchestration. This decision was not made lightly, as we were very impressed with your qualifications. However, we believe that this additional experience will be beneficial for the specific needs of our team at this time.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that your application was thoroughly reviewed. We were truly impressed by your skills and would like to keep your resume on file for future opportunities that may align with your expertise.\n\nThank you once again for your interest in our company, and we wish you the best in your job search and future endeavors. If you have any questions or need further assistance, please do not hesitate to reach out.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your",
