    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for this. it's a good start but it feels a little bit too standard/generic. i want to make it feel a bit more personalized so they actually feel valued, even though we're saying no. can you try a version that's a bit warmer? maybe acknowledge that it was a really close call between them and the other person?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior DevOps Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you in good spirits. I wanted to personally reach out and thank you for the time and effort you dedicated to the Senior DevOps role at our Austin office. Your enthusiasm and technical prowess truly shone through during our conversations, and we were genuinely impressed by your positive culture fit.\n\nThe decision-making process was indeed a close one, as we found ourselves weighing your impressive skill set against another candidate's slightly more extensive experience with Kubernetes orchestration. It's a tough call, and we wanted to ensure we made the best choice for our team. After much deliberation, we have decided to move forward with the other candidate.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly. Your qualifications were exceptional, and we were genuinely impressed by your dedication and passion. We will keep your resume on file and remain hopeful that a future opportunity may arise that aligns with your unique skill set.\n\nWe truly appreciate the time and effort you invested in our team, and we wish you the best in your job search and future endeavors. If you have any questions or need further assistance, please do not hesitate to reach out.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position",
      "source": "target",
